-------------------------- MODULE Allocator_InitMutex -----------------------------

CONSTANTS
  Client,     
  Resource    

VARIABLES
  unsat,       
  alloc        

-------------------------------------------------------------------------

Init ==
  /\ unsat = [c \in Client |-> {}]
  /\ alloc = [c \in Client |-> {}]

-------------------------------------------------------------------------

-------------------------------------------------------------------------

Mutex ==
  \A c1,c2 \in Client : \A r \in Resource :
     r \in alloc[c1] \cap alloc[c2] => c1 = c2

-------------------------------------------------------------------------

-------------------------------------------------------------------------

-------------------------------------------------------------------------

-------------------------------------------------------------------------

THEOREM InitMutex == Init => Mutex
PROOF
<1>1. ASSUME Init
      PROVE  Mutex
  <2>. USE DEF Mutex
  <2>1. TAKE c1 \in Client
  <2>2. TAKE c2 \in Client
  <2>3. TAKE r \in Resource
  <2>4. ASSUME r \in alloc[c1] \cap alloc[c2]
        PROVE  c1 = c2
    <3>1. alloc[c1] = {}
      BY <1>1 DEF Init
    <3>2. r \in {}
      BY <2>4, <3>1
    <3>3. FALSE
      BY <3>2
    <3>4. QED
      BY <3>3
  <2>5. QED
    BY <2>1, <2>2, <2>3, <2>4 DEF Mutex
<1>2. QED
  BY <1>1

=========================================================================
